text:
Hey all, I'm newer to HubSpot but have been working as a dev for a while. Trying to connect to the CRM API and keep getting the error "This app hasn't been granted all required scopes to make this call." Here's the error:

```{
   "status":"error",
   "message":"This app hasn't been granted all required scopes to make this call. Read more about required scopes here: <https://developers.HubSpot.com/scopes>.",
   "correlationId":"f2350aae-1480-4b3e-961b-59eb23b4d939",
   "errors":[
      {
         "message":"One or more of the following scopes are required.",
         "context":{
            "requiredScopes":[
               "media_bridge.read",
               "e-commerce",
               "contacts",
               "crm.objects.custom.read",
               "crm.objects.custom.write",
               "tickets"
            ]
         }
      }
   ],```

And I'm using the basic example from the HubSpot docs for fetching a deal:

```const getDeal = async (accessToken) =&gt; {
  const HubSpot = require('@HubSpot/api-client');
  const HubSpotClient = new HubSpot.Client({ apiKey: process.env.HubSpot_API_KEY });

  const limit = 10;
  const after = undefined;
  const properties = undefined;
  const propertiesWithHistory = undefined;
  const associations = undefined;
  const archived = false;

  try {
    const apiResponse = await HubSpotClient.crm.deals.basicApi.getPage(limit, after, properties, propertiesWithHistory, associations, archived);
    console.log(JSON.stringify(apiResponse.body, null, 2));
  } catch (e) {
    e.message === 'HTTP request failed'
      ? console.error(JSON.stringify(e.response, null, 2))
      : console.error(e)
  }};```
